data.enText: a chemical element. Nickel is a hard silver-white metal used in making some types of steel and other alloys .
a coin of the US and Canada worth 5 cents

tr: a United States coin worth one twentieth of a dollar
five dollars worth of a drug
a hard malleable ductile silvery metallic element that is resistant to corrosion
occurs in pentlandite and smaltite and garnierite and millerite

value.def: Nickel is a silver-coloured metal that is used in making steel.
In the United States and Canada, a nickel is a coin worth five cents.
